reviewText: Purchased for "Never Wave at a Wac" which was a major disappointment. Poorly written and generally uninteresting. "Four Guys Named Joe" depends a lot on Jane Wyman who is very long in the tooth for a young and eager airline stewardess. I would guess that her acceptance as an actress was a bizare aberation of the late 1940-50 period. The other two films are totally forgetable.
